remarks.para: This property can be used to alleviate a security threat. Some filters can be extremely expensive to evaluate or are very long-running. s are most often evaluated against a document from an untrusted source (SOAP message off the wire), which may be malicious. Because filters operate on XML documents, the best way to set computational limits on filter tables is to specify the maximum number of nodes that are examined while evaluating a filter in this table.

summary.para: Gets or sets the maximum number of XML document nodes that can be examined by the individual filters during a single call to a Match method. This value applies for each filter.
